The site at 317 Lester Avenue had been [permitted](https://www.buildzoom.com/property-info/317-lester-ave-oakland-ca) for the construction of a five-story building with 41 market-rate housing units. Athan Magganas, manager at the development firm Adelphos LLC, told [KQED](https://ww2.kqed.org/news/2016/10/31/massive-4-alarm-fire-near-oaklands-lake-merritt-causes-millions-of-dollars-in-damage/) that he estimated nearly $5 million in property damage. The site’s contractors are now out of work, and he is uncertain that Adelphos’s insurance policy will cover it.

This is the second construction project in Oakland to burn down this year. In July, [a fire](http://sfbamo.com/news/construction-site-in-emeryville-burns-down/) forestalled a project with 100 units on the Emeryville border.

